-- Stock funds worldwide attract $20.4 bln inflows in latest week -BofA
-- By Jennifer Ablan
-- Fri Oct 31, 2014 09:58AM EDT
-- None



NEW YORK, Oct 31 (Reuters) - Investors worldwide poured $20.4 billion into stock funds in the week ended Oct. 29, the largest in more than a year, data from a Bank of America Merrill Lynch Global Research report showed on Friday.

Bond funds worldwide attracted $6.5 billion, marking their sixth straight week of inflows, according to the report, which also cited data from fund-tracker EPFR Global. Emerging markets equity funds worldwide posted $1.3 billion of inflows after three straight weeks of outflows.